19 Sec. 13. Section 86-125, Revised Statutes Supplement, 2025, is
20 amended to read:
21 86-125 Notwithstanding the provisions of section 86-124:
22 (1) Any communications provider providing service in Nebraska shall
23 file a registration form with and pay a registration fee to the Public
24 Service Commission. Any communications provider shall register with the
25 commission prior to providing service. The commission shall prescribe the
26 registration form to be filed pursuant to this section;
27 (2) A communications provider providing the services described in
28 subdivision (8)(a) (7)(a) of this section shall provide the commission
29 with the name, address, telephone number, and email address of a contact
30 person concerning:
31 (a) The Nebraska Telecommunications Universal Service Fund Act and
-24-

AM2726 AM2726
LB1096 LB1096
JNH - 03/17/2026 JNH - 03/17/2026
1 related surcharges, if applicable;
2 (b) The Telecommunications Relay System Act and related surcharges,
3 if applicable;
4 (c) The 911 Service System Act and related surcharges, if
5 applicable; and
6 (d) Consumer complaints and inquiries;
7 (3) A communications provider providing the services described in
8 subdivision (8)(b) (7)(b) of this section shall provide the commission
9 with the name, address, telephone number, and email address of a person
10 with managerial responsibility for Nebraska operations;
11 (4) A communications provider shall:
12 (a) Submit a registration fee at the time of submission of the
13 registration form. The commission shall set the fee in an amount
14 sufficient to cover the costs of administering the registration process
15 but not to exceed fifty dollars;
16 (b) Keep the information required by this section current and notify
17 the commission of any changes to such information within sixty days after
18 the change; and
19 (c) Certify to the commission by January 1 each year that such
20 communications provider does not use or provide any communications
21 equipment or service deemed to pose a threat to national security
22 identified on the Covered List developed pursuant to 47 C.F.R. 1.50002,
23 as such regulation existed on January 1, 2023, and published by the
24 Public Safety and Homeland Security Bureau of the Federal Communications
25 Commission pursuant to the federal Secure and Trusted Communications
26 Networks Act of 2019, 47 U.S.C. 1601 et seq., as such act existed on
27 January 1, 2023, and the rules adopted pursuant to such act by the
28 Federal Communications Commission on November 11, 2022, in its Report and
29 Order FCC 22-84;
30 (5)(a) (5) The commission shall may, pursuant to section 75-156,
31 administratively fine any communications provider which violates
-25-

AM2726 AM2726
LB1096 LB1096
JNH - 03/17/2026 JNH - 03/17/2026
1 subdivision (4)(c) of this section. ;
2 (b) The commission may, pursuant to section 75-156, administratively
3 fine any communications provider which violates any other provision of
4 this section;
5 (6) Beginning November 8, 2026, in addition to other penalties and
6 relief provided by law, the Attorney General shall assess a civil penalty
7 of up to ten thousand dollars per day against any communications provider
8 that fails to submit the annual certification required under this section
9 or is unable to certify that its network is free of covered
10 communications equipment and services pursuant to subdivision (4)(c) of
11 this section;
12 (7) (6) This section applies to all communications providers
13 providing service in Nebraska except for those communications providers
